<item>
            <title>[TIKA-709] Tika network server does not print anything in response to, for example, Word documents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-709</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When trying to use Tika Server (java -jar tika-app-0.9.jar -t -p PORT) to parse M$Word DOC/DOCX files, tika server reads the file and then doesn&apos;t do anything more, it simply hangs, probably blocked on a socket read. This does not happend with, for example, HTML documents. I don&apos;t know the mechanics of this bug, but the following change definitely fixes the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Change&lt;br/&gt;
type.process(socket.getInputStream(), output);&lt;br/&gt;
to&lt;br/&gt;
type.process(new CloseShieldInputStream(socket.getInputStream()), output);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Debian Linux Sid&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
